[1]The church of Our Lady in Trier (in ), which is adjacent to the Saint-Pierre cathedral of Trier is a church built between 1235 and 1260 in the city of Trier, in Germany.With the cathedral of Magdeburg, it is one of the first examples of gothic architecture in Germany.
[2]His plan is based on the Greek cross, the tower above the dome, highlighting the intersection of the naves.
